    <h2>3) Background Skills</h2>
    <p>With your nationality selected, look at the background skills section. You may take 3+EDU modifier background skills at level 0.</p>

    <h2>4) Pre-Career Education</h2>
    <p>You may choose enter pre-career education. Allowing you to gain some skills and events before entering the workforce. Can also make entering certain careers easier. Different nations have different pre-career education options, and each nation should/will share a pre-career education table.</p>
    <p>While one usually enters pre-career education in the first term of their career, they may delay doing so until the third term at the latest, regardless of nation.</p>
    <h3>4.1) Roll of Entry</h3>
    <p>Roll to enter one pre-career education per term until your third term. Roll equal or greater then the educations Qualification stat</p>
    <h3>4.2) Gain Skills</h3>
    <p>You may choose one level 0 skill and one level 1 skill from the education skill list, as well as any other beenfits awarded from pre-career education.</p>
    <h3>4.3) Roll for an Event</h3>
    <p>The traveller then rolls on the Event Table for their nations pre-career education for this term.</p>
    <h3>4.4) Roll for graduation</h3>
    <p>The traveller then attempts to roll for gradution based on the Careers Graduation stat. If the traveller succeeds, they increase their chosen skills by one and gain any other benefits awarded with graduation.</p>
    <p>Some pre-career education also offers graduation with honours. Check if the career has this option and if so what is rewarded for doing so.</p>

    <h2>5) Choose a Career</h2>
    <p>Your traveller will go through one or more terms of Character creation. Each term represetnes 5 years of your charactesr life. Some careers may mention a minimum number of terms that you must be in.</p>
    <p>First you must choose a career to enter from the list for your nation <a href="/Career/">careers</a>.</p>
    <p>To enter a career, you roll against the Careers qualifacation stat, and then pick one of the assignments.</p>
    <p>You do not need to roll to enter your career each term. Only when you wish to change assignments within your career do you need to roll for entry again. If you fail to enter the new assignment then you only must stay in your current assignmnet.</p>
    <p>If you fail to enter an assignment, you must roll on your nations draft table.</p>

    <h2>6) First term in Career</h2>
    <p>If it is your First term in a career, you get basic training in that Career. If it is your first career, you get every skill in your Careers service skills at level 0. If this is not your first career, then pick one skill from your Careers Service Skill List.</p>

    <h2>7) Get Skill</h2>
    <p>Pick a skill table, either your assignments, the Personal Skill table, the Service Skills table, if you have a commission the Commission Skill Table, if you have an education above 10 in a Career with advanced education you can roll on your Careers Advanced Education Skill Table.</p>
    <p>Note your stats may never go above 3*(INT+EDU), during character creation you may never get a stat higher then 2*(INT+EDU)+3</p>

    <h2>8) Roll for Survival</h2>
    <p>Roll against your Assignments Survival attribute.</p>
    <p>If you fail, roll on your Careers mishap table, and then go to 13.</p>
    

